This paper deals with the problem of Quality-Sponsored Data (QSD) in a non-neutral network, which involves the economics of pricing and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes market dynamics and equilibria, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves pricing strategies, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the satisfaction of end-users, which could suggest it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
